text: Arizona's 19th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 29 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 87,941. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Lupe Contreras (D) and in the House of Representatives by Diego Espinoza (D) and Lorenzo Sierra (D). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 19th legislative district
